 2: Disable CSRF protection (not recommended)
If you&#39;re working on a stateless RESTful API or if you have other means of protecting against CSRF attacks, you can choose to disable CSRF protection altogether. However, this approach is not recommended unless you have alternative security measures in place. Here&#39;s an example of how to disable CSRF protection:

    @Configuration
