    CMD: ./test.sh
    ARGS: 1
    ARG1: 1
    ARG2:
    ARG3:

As you can see, args &quot;2&quot; and &quot;3&quot; are NOT passed to the script &quot;test.sh&quot;. You should have only used a 3 parameter `String[]`, the third parameter should be single value for the full command you want bash to run:

