    ARGS: 1 2 3
    ARG1: 1
    ARG2: 2
    ARG3: 3

BUT: the first line of test.sh `#!/bin/bash` tells the OS all it needs to know about running `test.sh`, so you can use the command directly and just separate out the arguments properly:

    start(new String[]{&quot;bin/test.sh&quot;, &quot;1&quot;,&quot;2&quot;,&quot;3&quot;}, null, System.out, null);
    CMD: bin/test.sh
    ARGS: 1 2 3
